ElementDescription: The NDAR Global Unique Identifier (GUID) for research subject
Subject ID how it's defined in lab/project
Age in months at the time of the interview/test/sampling/imaging.
Notes: Age is rounded to chronological month. If the research participant is 15-days-old at time of interview, the appropriate value would be 0 months. If the participant is 16-days-old, the value would be 1 month.

ElementDescription: Date on which the interview/genetic test/sampling/imaging/biospecimen was completed. MM/DD/YYYY
Sex of subject at birth
Notes: M = Male; F = Female; O=Other; NR = Not reported

ElementDescription: Auditory / Sounds: Responds negatively to unexpected or loud noises
Makes repetitive noises (ex. Humming)
Appears not to hear what other people say
Holds hands over ears
"Can't work with background noise (fan, refrigerator)"
Visual: Discomfort or avoids bright lights
Looks carefully or intensely at objects/people
Hesitates going up or down curbs or steps
Avoids eye contact
Taste: Deliberately smells objects
Chews/licks nonfood items
Movement: Becomes anxious or distressed when feet leave ground
Fears falling or heights
"Avoids climbing, jumping, bumpy or uneven ground"
Avoids playground equipment or moving toys
"Rocks unconsciously during other activities (i.e., watching TV)"
"Seeks out movement activities (whirled by adults, merry-go-round)"
"Touch: Avoids getting ""messy"" (paste, sand, finger paint, glue, tape)"
"Discomfort during grooming (hair cutting, face washing, fingernail cutting, tooth brushing)"
Sensitive to certain fabrics (centain clothes or bed sheets)
"Avoids going barefoot, especially in sand or grass"
"Picky eater, especially regarding textures"
Mouths objects
"Activity Level: Always ""on the go"""
"Prefers quiet, sedentary play (TV, books, computers)"
Difficulty paying attention
"Body Position: Hangs on people, furniture, objects even in familiar situations"
Walks on toes
Appears to enjoy falling
